      • resetall

        public void resetall()
        resets the ontology for all users: 1. perform update (=read from file) 2. delete all WorkSpaces and and Histories 3. delete all Beliefs that are referenced in all BeliefSpaces and all BeliefSpaces 4. delete all Beliefs which are not referenced in any BeliefSpace 5. create new WorkSpaces and BeliefSpaces for each user and initialize the WorkSpaces with the masteragenda 6. write the ontology to the file

      • reset

        public void reset(java.lang.String user)
        resets the ontology for one user: 1. perform update (=read from file) 2. delete all Beliefs that are referenced in the user's BeliefSpaces 3. delete the WorkSpace and BeliefSpace and Histories of the user 4. create new WorkSpace and BeliefSpace for the given user and initialize the WorkSpace with the masteragenda 5. write the ontology to the file
        Parameters:
        user - the user's name
